      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:2:8:1",
      "text": [
        " أَبَى اللَّهُ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ إِلَّا أَنْ يَجْعَلَ أَرْزَاقَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ مِنْ حَيْثُ لَا يَحْتَسِبُونَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, form his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Abu Ayoub Al Khazzaz, from Muhammad Bin Muslim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Allah<sup>azwj</sup> has Refused except that He<sup>azwj</sup> would Make the livelihoods of the Believers from where they did not reckon’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from abu Ayyub af-Khazzaz from Muhammad ibn Muslim who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that Allah, most Majestic, most Glorious, disdains to provide sustenance for a believing person from any source other than an unexpected source.” "
        ]
      }
    },
